La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.

Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Obtenga más información en https://texas.gov/covid19

post_text:
Breakfast: 7:30 a.m. to 9:30 a.m.
Lunch: Noon to 2 p.m.

Beginning Monday, March 23, 2020, each Varnett campus will provide free curbside breakfast and lunch. Vehicles will drive up to designated pickup points to collect the food. Breakfast will be distributed from 7:30 a.m. to 9:30 a.m. and lunch will be distributed from noon to 2 p.m. Monday through Friday.

Regulations require that a child must be in the vehicle in order to receive a meal. Those also eligible are children ages 18 years and younger and persons over 18 years of age who are determined by the State or local educational agency as having a mental or physical disability and who participate during the school year in a public or private non-profit school program established for the mentally or physically disabled.

Varnett will be closed at least through April 10, 2020 because of the coronavirus.

post_text:
Chess Math is an innovative learning process that teaches Varnett students math and chess at the same time. Coach James Hudson visits the 1st graders in Ms. Bobbie Estelle’s math class to teach them the values of each chess piece. Instead of asking the kids “What’s 5 + 3?”, he asks, “What’s Rook + Bishop?”, for example. There’s another by-product of Chess Math learning, kids gain chess skills, and some of them may move on to become members of the award-winning Varnett Chess Team.

#chess #math National Alliance for Public Charter Schools Texas Charter Schools Association Education Week Math Chess Chess.com #TEKS Texas Education Agency

text:
Chess Math is an innovative learning process that teaches Varnett students math and chess at the same time. Coach James Hudson visits the 1st graders in Ms. Bobbie Estelle’s math class to teach them the values of each chess piece. Instead of asking the kids “What’s 5 + 3?”, he asks, “What’s Rook + Bishop?”, for example. There’s another by-product of Chess Math learning, kids gain chess skills, and some of them may move on to become members of the award-winning Varnett Chess Team.

#chess #math National Alliance for Public Charter Schools Texas Charter Schools Association Education Week Math Chess Chess.com #TEKS Texas Education Agency

Chess Math Learning at Varnett Southwest Campus

Fathers, grandfathers, uncles and others came to the event to support their children. The event is one of the countless activities hosted by Varnett to promote family bonding and collaboration throughout the district. About 215 fathers from Southwest and Early Childhood Center attended.

Please join us in congratulating Mrs. Carlesa Bailey of the Early Childhood Center. She earned the "Employee Excellence Award" by a vote of her peers. The monthly award is designed to acknowledge and express appreciation for outstanding accomplishments that do not fall entirely within the scope of normal duties. Mrs. Bailey, a teacher assistant, was particularly credited for her teamwork.

"She goes over and beyond what is expected of her with a smile," says Mrs. Cheyne Brown, districtwide director of Early Childhood Education.
Congratulations, Mrs. Bailey!

post_text:
The Varnett School Southeast
Ms. Amber Green's third- through fifth-grade reading classes start off each week with vocabulary Monday. This week's activity was snowball vocabulary. The students wrote the vocabulary word and definitions on a piece of paper. Then they had to ball it up and throw it across the room. They were then asked to read the paper that had either a definition or word on it. If it had the word the students gave the teacher that definition. If it had a definition they gave the teacher the word.
Check it out!

#Varnett #literacy #reading #vocabulary #classroom #classroomfun #education #learning

FREE GROCERIES/ALIMENTOS GRATIS

Varnett Northeast Campus will have free groceries sponsored through the Houston Food Bank Mobile Pantry.
Monday September 30, 2019
8am-12pm
*Open to all*
You do not have to attend this school to receive groceries.

ALIMENTOS GRATIS
La escuela Northeast tendra alimentos gratuitos patrocinados a traves de la despensa movil de Houston Food Bank.
Lunes 30 de Septiembre de 2019
8am-12pm
*Abierto a todos*
No tiene que asistir a esta escuela para recibir alimentos.

The Houston Food Bank will send a refrigerated truck with milk, cereal and other grocery items.
When you arrive, you will be asked to sign in and a volunteer will assist you with grocery shopping.

El Banco de Alimentos de Houston enviará un camión refrigerado con leche, cereales y otros artículos comestibles. Cuando llegue, se le pedirá que inicie sesión y un voluntario lo ayudará con la compra de comestibles.

*Food Items will vary.
*Los artículos de supermercado variarán

post_text:
From knowing no English to speaking the language fluently

Jennifer Pineda, a Northeast student who received her fifth-grade diploma last week, says she didn't know a bit of English when she enrolled at Varnett as a third grader. Jennifer now speaks the language fluently. Listen as she tells her story in Spanish, and then English, during the fifth-grade promotion exercise at The Fellowship of Enlightenment Church. She credits her teachers and Varnett's application of the Rosetta Stone language program for her success.
